      "content": "## 3) Mechanistic basis (how it would interact with CYP2D6)\n- The **protonated primary amine** could engage in electrostatic/H-bond interactions in the CYP2D6 binding region.\n- However, the absence of **aromatic ring(s)** reduces the probability of strong hydrophobic/\u03c0 interactions that commonly stabilize inhibitor binding orientations near the heme.\n- The molecule may instead bind **weakly** or orient as a **metabolic substrate** (e.g., N-dealkylation/oxidation is less applicable here due to primary amine and lack of typical CYP2D6 substrate motifs; \u03c9/\u03c9-1 oxidation on the alkyl chain is more characteristic of other CYPs).",
